799
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:17,900
A ball.

800
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:19,870
O-Of course, it's a ball!

801
00:18:20,180 --> 00:18:21,900
Nicely done.

802
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:23,900
Even I could draw
something like that.

803
00:18:23,900 --> 00:18:26,820
There's no point if you're just copying others.

804
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,400
Kazama-kun!

805
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:29,790
Hey, Yoshinaga-sensei!

806
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:31,720
So what did you draw?

807
00:18:31,720 --> 00:18:33,750
I'm not really confident in it.

808
00:18:37,740 --> 00:18:40,260
Wow, you're very talented, Kazama-kun.

809
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:43,820
I personally don't think I got the color of the sky quite right though.

810
00:18:43,820 --> 00:18:45,340
Let me see it too.

811
00:18:45,340 --> 00:18:46,600
Hehe, he can see it.

812
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:49,230
It's not like seeing it will make his any better.

813
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:54,440
What do you think of my skills?

814
00:18:58,780 --> 00:19:00,120
What is it?

815
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:05,040
What's wrong with it?

816
00:19:05,460 --> 00:19:07,680
There's no heart in this drawing.

817
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:08,410
What?!

818
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:10,860
Are you nitpicking my drawing?!

819
00:19:10,860 --> 00:19:14,120
No, there's just no heart in it.

820
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:15,340
I'll add some in.

821
00:19:16,820 --> 00:19:21,130
Could I have been the one to discover Shin-chan's artistic talent?

822
00:19:21,380 --> 00:19:24,340
That's great, Shin-chan!
Try to put some heart into it!

